Defendant Latoya K Triblett in court.  Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz in court for Latoya K Triblett.  Prosecuting attorney Jessica Ann Behling in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
AS TO THE AMENDED COUNT 1: 
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he/she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he/she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 

Sentencing proceeds. Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant. 

Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 2 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 YEAR and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 1 YEAR. Credit given for 6 days time served if revoked.
.
COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 2 YEARS.
.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION: 
-provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges during probation; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-Court waived all non-mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges finding the defendant indigent;
-complete a parenting class;
-complete an anger management class;
-mental health assessment and cooperate with any treatment deemed necessary by the probation department;
-participate in individual therapy;
-follow all orders of DMCPS and/or Children Court Orders;
-contact with the victim will be as allowed through DMCPS.

Defendant informed she may not possess any firearms and body armor.
Defendant informed she may not vote in any election until civil rights have been reinstated.
.
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

Appeal rights given. Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Acknowledgment of ineligibility  Copies given to defendant. -- gmb
